Description: FRagment of oval handle to sharpish turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, worn. Name Astymedes. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0110.38.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (91)
